ca.uqac.lif.labpal

Class Laboratory

  • java.lang.Object
    • ca.uqac.lif.labpal.Laboratory
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ca.uqac.lif.petitpoucet.OwnershipManager

    public abstract class Laboratory
extends Object
implements ca.uqac.lif.petitpoucet.OwnershipManager
    A set of experiments, tables and plots. The lab is controlled by a lab assistant, which is responsible for running the experiments, populating the tables and drawing the plots.
    Author:
    Sylvain Hall√©

      • isEnvironmentOk

        public String isEnvironmentOk()
        Checks whether the environment for running the experiments in this lab is appropriate. Override this method if you want to check that some general conditions on the environment are met (such as: presence of some executable in the path, existence of a network connection, etc.).

        As a rule, returning false means that something external to the lab must be fixed before running the experiments; hence ParkBench will simply quit. If your experiments have prerequisites they can generate, don't use this method.

        Returns:
        null if the tests can be run, a String with an explanation otherwise.

      • countParkMips

        public static float countParkMips()
        Counts the number of "parkmips" of this system. This is a very rough indicator of the system's speed, measured in the number of increments of a long variable during a third of a second.

        ParkMips are designed to equal roughly 1 when run on an Asus Transformer Book T200 (yes, this is totally arbitrary).

        Returns:
        The number of parkmips
